   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>XXXI.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE TEST OF A FACTIOUS, SECTARIAN MAN</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>TITUS 3:10-11</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>We should refuse such a one after a first and second admonition, knowing that such a one has been perverted and sins, being self-condemned.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To refuse such a one is to exercise to quarantine him.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>When a believer is divisive, factious, sectarian, he becomes contagious; therefore, we need to refuse him, that is, to quarantine him.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>XXXII.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>THE TEST OF ANYONE</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>AMONG THE BELIEVERS BEING LED ASTRAY</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>FROM THE TRUTH</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>JAMES 5:19-20</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Someone should turn him back, knowing that he who turns a sinner back from the error of his way will save his soul from death, and will cover a multitude of sins.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>This is to restore from his sins a brother who is erring in the truth.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To do this requires love, spirituality, and adequate knowledge.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>XXXIII.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>THE TEST OF FALSE TEACHERS</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>AMONG THE BELIEVERS WHO SECRETLY BRING IN</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>DESTRUCTIVE HERESIES, EVEN DENYING THE</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>MASTER WHO BOUGHT THEM, AND MANY FOLLOWING</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>THEIR LICENTIOUSNESS, BECAUSE OF WHOM</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>THE WAY OF THE TRUTH WILL BE REVILED;</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>BY COVETOUSNESS WITH FABRICATED WORDS</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>THEY MAKE MERCHANDISE OF THE BELIEVERS</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>2 PETER 2:1-3</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The false teachers in this case were heretics in the ancient time, like today's modernists.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>For them the judgment of old is not idle, and their destruction does not slumber.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The believers should take Noah, a herald of righteousness, and righteous Lot as examples vv.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>5, 7 .</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>In a situation of destructive heresies, we should learn how to follow the faithful saints who stand fast in the truth against any kind of heresies.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>XXXIV.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>THE TEST OF MOCKERS MOCKING</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>ACCORDING TO THEIR OWN LUSTS, SAYING,</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>"WHERE IS THE PROMISE OF HIS COMING?"</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>2 PETER 3:3-4</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The truth is hidden from the heretical mockers by their own willfulness v. 5a . Because they are willfully ignorant, the truth in the word of God spoken by the prophets in the Scriptures is covered from their sight.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Therefore, Peter reminded the believers to remember the word of God spoken by the Old Testament prophets and the New Testament apostles vv.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>1-2, 5b, 7 .</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>This indicates that to take care of such a case of heresy, we need to help the believers to hold to the holy Word.</S>
   </TEXT>
